    <div class="section">
        <h2><a name="Overview"></a>Overview</h2>
	    <p>Built upon SQL Server 2008 R2 and delivered through Office SharePoint Server and Excel 2010, Microsoft PerformancePoint Server 2010 is a Business Intelligence application that puts business critical	information in the hands of users to monitor, analyse and plan.</p>
		<p>Using the Microsoft Business Intelligence platform, PerformancePoint Server 2010 can help you build an enterprise-grade, scalable performance management application. Using SQL Server 2008 R2 for data integration; an analytical data model that includes a calculation engine and data mining; and a highly flexible and scalable reporting platform to broadcast information to a wide audience. All of this is delivered via the Web in Microsoft Office SharePoint Server 2010, providing everyone with a central place to get their business intelligence information.</p>
        <p>Complex data can be presented simply through Microsoft Excel or SharePoint webparts to allow effective monitoring, analysing and planning of your business. Out-of-the-box tools can be used to simply build customised dashboards and scorecards giving users the information they need to make the right decisions. Data can be manipulated in Excel and written back to OLAP cubes allowing users to consider multiple forecasts based on countless different scenarios.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2><a name="Features"></a>Features</h2>

		<h3>Monitor</h3>
		<p>You can use Microsoft Office PerformancePoint Server 2010 to build highly visual and interactive scorecards and dashboards that can keep you up to date on critical business information and how it relates to the overall performance of your organization. <br />
		You be easily alerted to information that shows where the business is meeting, or failing to meet specified	goals.</p>
		
		<h3>Analyse</h3>
		<p>Step from merely monitoring data and dig deeply into the reasons why a part of your business is performing in such a way through the analytics PerformancePoint Server offers.</p>
    </div>

